<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  metal:use-macro="view/macro:page/main_only"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <div class="top-portlet">
    <tal:permissions replace="
        structure
        context/product/@@+portlet-not-using-launchpad"/>
  </div>

  <p>Before uploading any translations, please read the
    <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/Translations/ImportPolicy"
       >translations import policy</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Upload either a single file (<code>.pot</code> /
    <code>.po</code>) or a tar file containing a PO template and a set of PO
    files (<code>.tar</code>, <code>.tar.gz</code>, <code>.tgz</code> or
    <code>.tar.bz2</code>).
    The files you upload will be reviewed by an admin before they appear in
    Launchpad.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you want to avoid manual review of your templates and translations,
    we suggest you set up an
    <a tal:attributes="
        href string:${context/fmt:url}/+translations-settings"
       >automatic</a> import from a bazaar branch instead
    (<a href="
       https://help.launchpad.net/Translations/ImportingFromBazaarBranches"
        >read more</a>).
  </p>

  <form action="+translations-upload" method="post"
        enctype="multipart/form-data" class="translations">
    <div class="fields">
      <label for="file_input">File:</label>
      <input id="file_input" name="file" type="file" />
    </div>
    <div class="actions">
      <p>
        <input name="translations_upload" type="submit"
               value="Upload"/>
        or <a tal:attributes="href view/cancel_url">Cancel</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>

</body>
</html>
